import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
title: "About ContractorSoftwareHub"
description: "Independent software reviews for contractors who need straight answers, not marketing copy."
---

<header class="bg-[#0f172a] text-white">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">About ContractorSoftwareHub</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-300">Independent software reviews for contractors who need straight answers, not marketing copy.</p>
  </div>
</header>

<main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
  <section class="mb-12">
    <p class="text-lg mb-6">Most contractor software reviews are useless.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">They're either written by someone who has never actually run a service business, or they're effectively vendor content — carefully worded to say nothing negative about any product that might be paying an affiliate commission. You end up reading four comparison articles and knowing less than when you started.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">That's what ContractorSoftwareHub is trying to fix.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">I'm Chris Harper. I started this site after spending more time than I'd like to admit trying to find honest, specific information about contractor software — and consistently coming up empty. What I found instead was a lot of articles that listed the same six tools, described each one's features in language lifted directly from the vendor's own website, and concluded with a recommendation based on nothing.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What we actually do here</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">We aggregate real feedback from contractors who use this software every day. Every review on ContractorSoftwareHub follows the same process:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-3 ml-5">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="text-[#22c55e] font-bold mt-0.5">1.</span>
        <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>We sign up for trials</strong> — or at least go deep enough on demos, pricing pages, and documentation to understand the real capabilities.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="text-[#22c55e] font-bold mt-0.5">2.</span>
        <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>We read hundreds of reviews</strong> — filtering G2 and Capterra feedback for patterns from real contractors, not paid promoters.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="text-[#22c55e] font-bold mt-0.5">3.</span>
        <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>We analyze pricing honestly</strong> — including the hidden fees, tier restrictions, and contract terms vendors don't advertise.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="text-[#22c55e] font-bold mt-0.5">4.</span>
        <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>We say who it's wrong for</strong> — every review includes a clear "not for" section so you can disqualify tools that don't fit your operation.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How we make money</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">ContractorSoftwareHub earns affiliate commissions when you click through to a software product and sign up. That's disclosed on every article and on our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/" class="text-[#0f172a] underline hover:text-[#22c55e]">affiliate disclosure page</a>.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">This means we have a financial incentive to be helpful enough that you trust the recommendation — because if the reviews aren't useful, you don't click, and the whole thing falls apart. A bad tool gets a critical review here, regardless of commission rates.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Who this is for</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Painting contractors, electricians, plumbers, HVAC technicians, roofers, landscapers, general contractors — anyone running a real service business who needs to choose software without sitting through six vendor demos to get a straight answer.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Get in touch</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Questions or feedback? Use the <a href="/contact/" class="text-[#0f172a] underline hover:text-[#22c55e]">contact page</a>. If you've used a tool we haven't reviewed, or you think we got something wrong, say so.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700">— Chris Harper | ContractorSoftwareHub.com</p>
  </section>
</main>

